Package tk.artsakenos.ultrahttp.drupal

Class DrupalNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • tk.artsakenos.ultrahttp.drupal.DrupalNode
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable
    public class DrupalNode
extends Object
implements Serializable
    Extend it you should override DrupalNode(String json), and toJsonNode() (not toJsonString() that uses it). NOTE: Why not to use the normal mappers? Because all the Drupal object are wrapped in crazy way to exploit multi-fields, languages, and other crazy things. 
     // Example of fields, native fields are already there (title body, summary, ...)
 public String field_code_iris;
 public Integer field_year;
 public Boolean field_international_coauthors;
 public List{Long} field_entities = new ArrayList{}(); // Autori structured
 [...]
 public DrupalPublication(String json) {
      super(json);
      JsonNode jsonNode = Jsonable.getJsonNodeByPath(json, "");
      field_code_iris = getText(jsonNode, "field_code_iris", "value");
      field_year = getInt(jsonNode, "field_year", "value");
      field_international_coauthors = getBoolean(jsonNode, "field_international_coauthors", "value");
      field_entities = getArray(jsonNode, "field_entities", "target_id", field_entities, Long.class);
      field_url = getText(jsonNode, "field_url", "uri"); // Custom field should be inspected with a rest client)
 [...]
 public ObjectNode toJsonNode() {
      ObjectNode jsonNode = super.toJsonNode();
      set(jsonNode, "field_code_iris", "value", field_code_iris);
      set(jsonNode, "field_year", "value", field_year);
      set(jsonNode, "field_international_coauthors", "value", field_international_coauthors);
      set(jsonNode, "field_url", "uri", field_url);
      setArray(jsonNode, "field_entities", "target_id", field_entities);
      setArray(jsonNode, "field_publication_type", "target_id", field_publication_type);
 [...]
 // Field optional can be used like this:
 public DrupalPublication(String json) {
      optionalSet(jsonNode); // field_optional is already included
 public ObjectNode toJsonNode() {
      set(jsonNode, "field_optional", "value", Jsonable.toJson(optionalRetrieve(), true));
 return jsonNode;
 }

      • getText

        public final String getText​(com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.JsonNode jsonNode,
                            String fieldName,
                            String valueName)
        Drupal inserisce i value in un oggetto del tipo: "field_name": [ { "value": "field value" }. Questo metodo si occupa di controllare che il campo esista e di effettuare la get. Funziona solo con i campidi testo e con un solo elemento!
        Parameters:
        fieldName - Il fieldName
        valueName - Il valueName (e.g., value, target_id)
